# Minimalist Gym Progression Engine

Production-ready baseline for a mobile-first Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind + Supabase app.

## 1) Environment variables

Create a `.env.local` file at the project root:

```bash
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_ID.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
```

> Do not use a service role key in this app.

## Required Supabase environment variables

The app requires these variables:

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`

Set them in both:

- `.env.local` for local development
- Vercel **Environment Variables** for deployments

## 2) Run locally

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Then open `http://localhost:3000`.

## 3) Apply migration

This project includes SQL migration:

- `supabase/migrations/001_init.sql`

Apply it with Supabase CLI (linked project) or copy/paste into the Supabase SQL editor.

Example CLI flow:

```bash
supabase login
supabase link --project-ref YOUR_PROJECT_REF
supabase db push
```

## 4) Build and deploy

Deploy the Next.js app to Vercel (recommended) or any Node-compatible host.

- Add the same `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` env vars in deployment settings.
- Run build command:

```bash
npm run build
```

- Start command:

```bash
npm run start
```

## Included baseline features

- Email/password login + sign up page (`/login`)
- Auth-protected app routes (`/today`, `/session/[id]`, `/history`, `/settings`)
- Start session flow from `/today`
- Set logging in `/session/[id]`
- Recent sessions list in `/history`
- Email display + sign out in `/settings`
